# pyenv
#   For a library or app, you might want to share your .python-version if you're
#   using tools like pyenv. However, it's sometimes better to ignore it:
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if used with a library, you may want to ignore it:
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipenv, poetry.lock contains exact versions of dependencies.
#   It is typically recommended to check in poetry.lock.
#poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipenv and Poetry, pdm.lock contains exact versions of dependencies.
#pdm.lock

